last_known_value.value: Crossed TPM / RPM / Max Parallel Request Limit
Missing litellm-enterprise package. Please install it to use this feature. Run `pip install litellm-enterprise`
This uses the enterprise folder - only available on the Docker image.
Admin-only endpoint. Not allowed to access this.

You must be a LiteLLM Enterprise user to use this feature. If you have a license please set `LITELLM_LICENSE` in your env. Get a 7 day trial key here: https://www.litellm.ai/enterprise#trial. 
Pricing: https://www.litellm.ai/#pricing
Optional[dict] - Model aliases for the user - [Docs](https://litellm.vercel.app/docs/proxy/virtual_keys#model-aliases)
Optional[list] - List of allowed cache control values. Example - ["no-cache", "no-store"]. See all values - https://docs.litellm.ai/docs/proxy/caching#turn-on--off-caching-per-request-
bool - Default=True. Flag used for returning a key as part of the /user/new response
Optional[bool] - [Not Implemented Yet] Whether the user is blocked.

Optional[str] - Budget is reset at the end of specified duration. If not set, budget is never reset. You can set duration as seconds ("30s"), minutes ("30m"), hours ("30h"), days ("30d"), months ("1mo").
Optional[str] - Duration for the key auto-created on `/user/new`. Default is None.
Optional[List[str]] - [Not Implemented Yet] List of active guardrails for the user
Optional[float] - Specify max budget for a given user.
Optional[int] - Rate limit a user based on the number of parallel requests. Raises 429 error, if user's parallel requests > x.
Optional[dict] - Metadata for user, store information for user. Example metadata = {"team": "core-infra", "app": "app2", "email": "ishaan@berri.ai" }
Optional[dict] - Model-specific max budget for user. [Docs](https://docs.litellm.ai/docs/proxy/users#add-model-specific-budgets-to-keys)
Optional[float] - Model-specific rpm limit for user. [Docs](https://docs.litellm.ai/docs/proxy/users#add-model-specific-limits-to-keys)
Optional[float] - Model-specific tpm limit for user. [Docs](https://docs.litellm.ai/docs/proxy/users#add-model-specific-limits-to-keys)
Optional[list] - Model_name's a user is allowed to call. (if empty, key is allowed to call all models)
Optional[dict] - [Not Implemented Yet] User-specific permissions, eg. turning off pii masking.
Optional[int] - Specify rpm limit for a given user (Requests per minute)
Optional[bool] - Specify if an invite email should be sent.
Optional[float] - Get alerts when user crosses given budget, doesn't block requests.
Optional[float] - Amount spent by user. Default is 0. Will be updated by proxy whenever user is used.
Optional[str] - [DEPRECATED PARAM] The team id of the user. Default is None.
Optional[list] - specify a list of team id's a user belongs to.
Optional[int] - Specify tpm limit for a given user (Tokens per minute)
Optional[str] - A descriptive name for you to know who this user id refers to.
Optional[str] - Specify a user id. If not set, a unique id will be generated.

Optional[str] - Specify a user role - "proxy_admin", "proxy_admin_viewer", "internal_user", "internal_user_viewer", "team", "customer". Info about each role here: `https://github.com/BerriAI/litellm/litellm/proxy/_types.py#L20`
